I&#39;ve implemented a builder which is able to build/construct JSON objects dynamically, by importing different forms of `key` - `value` pairs and applying them on top of each other (see the below attached source as well as some unit tests for it). It can be easily extended if you need to.

The attached code is at its initial version which supports up to 3 forms of `importing key-value pairs`. The actual library is not published yet but it will be soon.

Related to your case, for example, you can build your JSON object like so (I&#39;ve added more fields there just to demonstrate more ways of appending data):
```java
